hwhqosIfStatTable.name: hwhqosIfStatTable
hwhqosIfStatTable.description: Table of Hierarchy QoS's statistic information.

hwhqosIfStatEntry.name: hwhqosIfStatEntry
hwhqosIfStatEntry.description: The table have multilevel index if don't have some or other index. please fill the MAX value 2147483647 for example : MA52 don't have statistic of user's queue, but have statistic of user. please set QueueIndex the MAX value 2147483647.

hwhqosIfIndex.name: hwhqosIfIndex
hwhqosIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of an interface. The interface can be a physical interface or a logical interface.

hwhqosDirection.name: hwhqosDirection
hwhqosDirection.description: The value of this object identifies the incoming and outgoing directions. The object can be set to 0 when the direction is not specified.

hwhqosUserLayer1.name: hwhqosUserLayer1
hwhqosUserLayer1.description: The value of this object identifies the outer identifier of a user group.

hwhqosUserLayer2.name: hwhqosUserLayer2
hwhqosUserLayer2.description: The value of this object identifies the outer identifier of a user.

hwhqosQueueIndex.name: hwhqosQueueIndex
hwhqosQueueIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the queue index of a user. Each user has multiple queues and the index indicates the queues for each user. Each user of the NE40E has eight queues. If this object does not exist, you can set it to 0.

hwhqosQueueForwardPackets.name: hwhqosQueueForwardPackets
hwhqosQueueForwardPackets.description: The value of this object identifies the packets forwarded in the queue. If this object is not supported, fill 0.

hwhqosQueueForwardBytes.name: hwhqosQueueForwardBytes
hwhqosQueueForwardBytes.description: The value of this object identifies the bytes forwarded in the queue. If this object is not supported, fill 0.

hwhqosQueueDropPackets.name: hwhqosQueueDropPackets
hwhqosQueueDropPackets.description: This object indicates the number of packets discarded from the queue. If this object is not supported, fill 0.

hwhqosQueueDropBytes.name: hwhqosQueueDropBytes
hwhqosQueueDropBytes.description: This object indicates the number of bytes discarded from the queue. If this object is not supported, fill 0.

hwhqosQueueRemarkPackets.name: hwhqosQueueRemarkPackets
hwhqosQueueRemarkPackets.description: RemarkPackets number of queue. if not support, please fill 0.

hwhqosQueueRemarkBytes.name: hwhqosQueueRemarkBytes
hwhqosQueueRemarkBytes.description: RemarkBytes number of queue. if not support, please fill 0.

hwhqosSetZero.name: hwhqosSetZero
hwhqosSetZero.description: This object indicates that the statistics are cleared.

hwhqosQueueForwardPacketRate.name: hwhqosQueueForwardPacketRate
hwhqosQueueForwardPacketRate.description: This object indicates the packet forwarding rate in the queue, in pps.

hwhqosQueueForwardByteRate.name: hwhqosQueueForwardByteRate
hwhqosQueueForwardByteRate.description: This object indicates the byte forwarding rate in the queue, in bps.

hwhqosQueueDropPacketRate.name: hwhqosQueueDropPacketRate
hwhqosQueueDropPacketRate.description: This object indicates the packet discarding rate in the queue, in pps.

hwhqosQueueDropByteRate.name: hwhqosQueueDropByteRate
hwhqosQueueDropByteRate.description: This object indicates the byte discarding rate in the queue, in bps.

hwhqosAtmPvcStatTable.name: hwhqosAtmPvcStatTable
hwhqosAtmPvcStatTable.description: Table of Hierarchy QoS's statistic information.

hwhqosAtmPvcStatEntry.name: hwhqosAtmPvcStatEntry
hwhqosAtmPvcStatEntry.description: The table have multilevel index if don't have some or other index. please fill the MAX value 2147483647 for example : MA52 don't have statistic of user's queue, but have statistic of user. please set QueueIndex the MAX value 2147483647.

hwhqosAtmPvcDirection.name: hwhqosAtmPvcDirection
hwhqosAtmPvcDirection.description: Direction: inbound;outbound. if don't have, please fill 255.

hwhqosAtmPvcUserLayer1.name: hwhqosAtmPvcUserLayer1
hwhqosAtmPvcUserLayer1.description: Usergroupid: just the Usergroup's configure sequence Usergroupname is identifier in Hierarchy QoS.

hwhqosAtmPvcUserLayer2.name: hwhqosAtmPvcUserLayer2
hwhqosAtmPvcUserLayer2.description: Userid: just the User's configure sequence Username is identifier in Hierarchy QoS.

hwhqosAtmPvcQueueIndex.name: hwhqosAtmPvcQueueIndex
hwhqosAtmPvcQueueIndex.description: index of user's queue. 8031: everyuser have 4 queues MA52: everyuser have 8 queues 8090: everyuser have 8 queues if don't have, please fill 0.

hwhqosAtmPvcQueueForwardPackets.name: hwhqosAtmPvcQueueForwardPackets
hwhqosAtmPvcQueueForwardPackets.description: ForwardPackets number of queue. if not support, please fill 0.

hwhqosAtmPvcQueueForwardBytes.name: hwhqosAtmPvcQueueForwardBytes
hwhqosAtmPvcQueueForwardBytes.description: ForwardBytes number of queue. if not support, please fill 0.

hwhqosAtmPvcQueueDropPackets.name: hwhqosAtmPvcQueueDropPackets
hwhqosAtmPvcQueueDropPackets.description: DropPackets number of queue. if not support, please fill 0.

hwhqosAtmPvcQueueDropBytes.name: hwhqosAtmPvcQueueDropBytes
hwhqosAtmPvcQueueDropBytes.description: DropBytes number of queue. if not support, please fill 0.

hwhqosAtmPvcQueueRemarkPackets.name: hwhqosAtmPvcQueueRemarkPackets
hwhqosAtmPvcQueueRemarkPackets.description: RemarkPackets number of queue. if not support, please fill 0.

hwhqosAtmPvcQueueRemarkBytes.name: hwhqosAtmPvcQueueRemarkBytes
hwhqosAtmPvcQueueRemarkBytes.description: RemarkBytes number of queue. if not support, please fill 0.

hwhqosPortQueueTable.name: hwhqosPortQueueTable
hwhqosPortQueueTable.description: Table of configuration about a port-queue.

hwhqosPortQueueEntry.name: hwhqosPortQueueEntry
hwhqosPortQueueEntry.description: Information about configuration of an interface cos-queue.

hwhqosPortQueueIfIndex.name: hwhqosPortQueueIfIndex
hwhqosPortQueueIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of a physical port.The value ranges from 0 to 2147483647.

hwhqosPortQueueCosValue.name: hwhqosPortQueueCosValue
hwhqosPortQueueCosValue.description: The value of this object identifies the queue type.The value can be any of the following: portqueueBE(1) portqueueAF1(2) portqueueAF2(3) portqueueAF3(4) portqueueAF4(5) portqueueEF(6) portqueueCS6(7) portqueueCS7(8)

hwhqosPortQueueArithmetic.name: hwhqosPortQueueArithmetic
hwhqosPortQueueArithmetic.description: The value of this object identifies the queue scheduling arithmetic. The value can be any of the following: portqueuePQ(1) portqueueWFQ(2) portqueueLPQ(3)

hwhqosPortQueueWeightValue.name: hwhqosPortQueueWeightValue
hwhqosPortQueueWeightValue.description: The value of this object identifies the weight of the Weighted Fair Queuing (WFQ) scheduling arithmetic.

hwhqosPortQueueShaValue.name: hwhqosPortQueueShaValue
hwhqosPortQueueShaValue.description: The value of this object identifies the bandwidth allocated to the queue.

hwhqosPortQueueShaPercent.name: hwhqosPortQueueShaPercent
hwhqosPortQueueShaPercent.description: The value of this object identifies the proportion of the queue bandwidth to the bandwidth of the port.

hwhqosPortQueueWredName.name: hwhqosPortQueueWredName
hwhqosPortQueueWredName.description: This object indicates the name of the Weighted Random Early Detection (WRED) template. The object is a string of 1 to 31 characters.

hwhqosPortQueuePbsValue.name: hwhqosPortQueuePbsValue
hwhqosPortQueuePbsValue.description: The object specifies the value of the port-queue specific queue pbs.

hwhqosPortQueueRowStatus.name: hwhqosPortQueueRowStatus
hwhqosPortQueueRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status.

hwhqosWredTable.name: hwhqosWredTable
hwhqosWredTable.description: Table of configuration about a wred template.

hwhqosWredEntry.name: hwhqosWredEntry
hwhqosWredEntry.description: Information about configuration of the value of wred color .

hwhqosWredName.name: hwhqosWredName
hwhqosWredName.description: The value of this object identifies the name of the WRED template. The object is a string of 1 to 31 characters.

hwhqosWredGreenLowLimit.name: hwhqosWredGreenLowLimit
hwhqosWredGreenLowLimit.description: The value of this object identifies the lower threshold of the green port queue.

hwhqosWredGreenHighLimit.name: hwhqosWredGreenHighLimit
hwhqosWredGreenHighLimit.description: The value of this object identifies the upper threshold of the green port queue.

hwhqosWredGreenDiscardPercent.name: hwhqosWredGreenDiscardPercent
hwhqosWredGreenDiscardPercent.description: The value of this object identifies the packet loss ratio between the upper threshold and the lower threshold of the green port queue.

hwhqosWredYellowLowLimit.name: hwhqosWredYellowLowLimit
hwhqosWredYellowLowLimit.description: The value of this object identifies the lower threshold of the yellow port queue.

hwhqosWredYellowHighLimit.name: hwhqosWredYellowHighLimit
hwhqosWredYellowHighLimit.description: The value of this object identifies the upper threshold of the yellow port queue.

hwhqosWredYellowDiscardPercent.name: hwhqosWredYellowDiscardPercent
hwhqosWredYellowDiscardPercent.description: The value of this object identifies the packet loss ratio between the upper threshold and the lower threshold of the yellow port queue.

hwhqosWredRedLowLimit.name: hwhqosWredRedLowLimit
hwhqosWredRedLowLimit.description: The value of this object identifies the lower threshold of the red port queue.

hwhqosWredRedHighLimit.name: hwhqosWredRedHighLimit
hwhqosWredRedHighLimit.description: The value of this object identifies the upper threshold of the red port queue.

hwhqosWredRedDiscardPercent.name: hwhqosWredRedDiscardPercent
hwhqosWredRedDiscardPercent.description: The value of this object identifies the packet loss ratio between the upper threshold and the lower threshold of the red port queue.

hwhqosWredRowStatus.name: hwhqosWredRowStatus
hwhqosWredRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status.

hwhqosIfQueueStatQueueIndex.name: hwhqosIfQueueStatQueueIndex
hwhqosIfQueueStatQueueIndex.description: Index number of queues with priority. The values and meanings are as follows: 1 be 2 af1 3 af2 4 af3 5 af4 6 ef 7 cs6 8 cs7

hwhqosUserQueueStatType.name: hwhqosUserQueueStatType
hwhqosUserQueueStatType.description: Types of statistic: interface(1), mactunel(2), userclassifier(3)

hwhqosUserQueueStatNameString.name: hwhqosUserQueueStatNameString
hwhqosUserQueueStatNameString.description: Name character string: If the statistic is based on mac-tunnel, this field is the name of the mac-tunnel. If the statistic is based on user classification, this field is the name of the user classification. If the statistic is based on an interface, this field is the name of the interface.

hwhqosUserQueueStatDirection.name: hwhqosUserQueueStatDirection
hwhqosUserQueueStatDirection.description: Direction: If the statistic is based on user classification, the direction is divided to upstream (1) and downstream (2). If the Statistic is based on mac-tunnel, the direction is applied only on the downstream (2).

hwhqosUserQueueStatQueueIndex.name: hwhqosUserQueueStatQueueIndex
hwhqosUserQueueStatQueueIndex.description: Index number of the queues. The values and meanings are as follows: 1 be 2 af1 3 af2 4 af3 5 af4 6 ef 7 cs6 8 cs7 9 total

hwhqosUserQueueStatForwardPackets.name: hwhqosUserQueueStatForwardPackets
hwhqosUserQueueStatForwardPackets.description: The number of packets that pass through.

hwhqosUserQueueStatForwardBytes.name: hwhqosUserQueueStatForwardBytes
hwhqosUserQueueStatForwardBytes.description: The number of bytes that pass through.

hwhqosUserQueueStatReset.name: hwhqosUserQueueStatReset
hwhqosUserQueueStatReset.description: Counter resetting. If the value is 1, the object resets the statistics through the set operation. It is no of use to access the value of this object.

hwhqosUserQueueStatLastResetTime.name: hwhqosUserQueueStatLastResetTime
hwhqosUserQueueStatLastResetTime.description: The time stamp that the counter is reset last.

hwhqosUserQueueStatPerDropPackets.name: hwhqosUserQueueStatPerDropPackets
hwhqosUserQueueStatPerDropPackets.description: The number of discarded packets in a certain period.

hwhqosUserGroupQueueStatEntry.name: hwhqosUserGroupQueueStatEntry
hwhqosUserGroupQueueStatEntry.description: user group queue statistic table entry

hwhqosUserGroupQueueForwardPackets.name: hwhqosUserGroupQueueForwardPackets
hwhqosUserGroupQueueForwardPackets.description: The number of packets that pass through.

hwhqosUserGroupQueueForwardBytes.name: hwhqosUserGroupQueueForwardBytes
hwhqosUserGroupQueueForwardBytes.description: The number of bytes that pass through.

hwhqosUserGroupQueueStatReset.name: hwhqosUserGroupQueueStatReset
hwhqosUserGroupQueueStatReset.description: Counter resetting. If the value is reset(1), the object resets the statistics through the set operation. It is no of use to access the value of this object.

hwhqosUserGroupQueueStatLastResetTime.name: hwhqosUserGroupQueueStatLastResetTime
hwhqosUserGroupQueueStatLastResetTime.description: The time stamp that the counter is reset last.

hwVPNHQoSVPNType.description: VPN Type: Tunnel (0), L3VPN (1), VPLS (2), VLL(3);

hwVPNHQoSPassBytes.name: hwVPNHQoSPassBytes

hwhqosTunnelVPNType.description: VPN Type: Tunnel (0), L3VPN (1), VPLS (2), VLL(3);

hwhqosTunnelPassedByteRate.description: Rate of bytes passed of enqueue. Unit: Bps

hwhqosFolwMappingCfgQueueCosValue.description: This object indicates the service type of a class queue.

hwhqosFlowMappingCfgPortQueueCosValue.description: This object indicates the service type of a port queue.

hwhqosFlowQueueRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status. Currently, three row statuses are supported: Active, CreateAndGo, and Destroy.

hwhqosFlowQueueCfgCosValue.name: hwhqosFlowQueueCfgCosValue
hwhqosFlowQueueCfgCosValue.description: This object indicates the configured priority of a flow queue.

hwhqosFlowQueueCfgType.name: hwhqosFlowQueueCfgType
hwhqosFlowQueueCfgType.description: This object indicates the scheduling mode of a flow queue.

hwhqosFlowQueueCfgWeightValue.name: hwhqosFlowQueueCfgWeightValue
hwhqosFlowQueueCfgWeightValue.description: The value of this object identifies the WFQ scheduling weight.

hwhqosFlowQueueCfgShapingValue.name: hwhqosFlowQueueCfgShapingValue
hwhqosFlowQueueCfgShapingValue.description: The value of this object identifies the shaping rate, namely, the configured interface bandwidth. The value of this object is equal to the PIR value.

hwhqosFlowQueueCfgShapingPercentageValue.name: hwhqosFlowQueueCfgShapingPercentageValue
hwhqosFlowQueueCfgShapingPercentageValue.description: The value of this object identifies the percentage of the shaping rate, that is, the percentage of the traffic-shaping bandwidth to the interface bandwidth.

hwhqosFlowQueueCfgWredName.name: hwhqosFlowQueueCfgWredName
hwhqosFlowQueueCfgWredName.description: The value of this object identifies the WRED object used by a flow queue.

hwhqosFlowQueueCfgPbsValue.name: hwhqosFlowQueueCfgPbsValue
hwhqosFlowQueueCfgPbsValue.description: The object specifies the value of the flow-queue specific queue pbs.

hwhqosFlowQueueCfgRowStatus.name: hwhqosFlowQueueCfgRowStatus
hwhqosFlowQueueCfgRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status. Currently, three row statuses are supported: Active, CreateAndGo, and Destroy.

hwhqosFlowWredRowStatus.name: hwhqosFlowWredRowStatus

hwhqosFlowWredColor.name: hwhqosFlowWredColor
hwhqosFlowWredColor.description: This object indicates the color for marking packets.

hwhqosFlowWredColorLowlimitPercentage.name: hwhqosFlowWredColorLowlimitPercentage
hwhqosFlowWredColorLowlimitPercentage.description: The value of this object identifies the percentage of the WRED lower threshold, that is, the percentage of the WRED lower threshold to the flow queue length. When the average queue length reaches this number, packets are discarded.

hwhqosFlowWredColorHighlimitPercentage.name: hwhqosFlowWredColorHighlimitPercentage
hwhqosFlowWredColorHighlimitPercentage.description: The value of this object identifies the percentage of the WRED upper threshold, that is, the percentage of the WRED upper threshold to the flow queue length. When the average queue length reaches this number, packets are discarded.

hwhqosFlowWredColorDiscardPercentage.name: hwhqosFlowWredColorDiscardPercentage
hwhqosFlowWredColorDiscardPercentage.description: The value of this object identifies the percentage of the packets that are discarded by WRED.

hwhqosFlowWredColorRowStatus.name: hwhqosFlowWredColorRowStatus
hwhqosFlowWredColorRowStatus.description: This object indicates the row status. Currently, three row statuses are supported: Active, CreateAndGo, and Destroy.

hwhqosUserQueuePirValue.description: The value of this object identifies the PIR of a user queue.

hwhqosUserQueueFlowMappingName.name: hwhqosUserQueueFlowMappingName
